cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.HC, cs.CL 

The paper focuses on the automatic analysis of multimedia content, specifically micro-videos, which suggests that it could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) or Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of computational features and machine learning algorithms to detect creative content, which could fall under Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper involves the use of crowdsourcing to create a dataset, which could also relate to Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) in terms of natural language processing and annotation.
